<item>
            <title>[AMQ-3342] Shutdown of broker waiting for shared fileystem lock blocks</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-3342</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Shutting down a broker that has not completed startup due to waiting for a shared filesystem lock does not complete.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using an internal BrokerService() and it&apos;s stop() method is definitely impacted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The attached patch simply adds a check for &quot;isStopped() || isStopping()&quot; to the MessageDatabase lock loop.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
